raw_data.title: CADD Designer
raw_data.description: Prepares drawing of unique, complex or original designs which require a high degree of precision using AutoCAD to create plans and models. Keeps up with CAD trends, arranging and attending meetings with collaborators and managers, creating models or drawings with CAD software, optimizing workflows with their team and other teams in the company. Gathers reference information from other teams or clients, making revisions to drawings, or keeping a database of design records.  Performs usually difficult assignments requiring considerable initiative, resourcefulness and drafting expertise.

raw_data.description: Provides day-to-day direction and control of IT and/or Security System projects. raw_data.title: Subject Matter Expert
raw_data.description: Provides mission-critical subject matter support for complex IT and Security System initiatives. Has demonstrated expertise in participating successfully on similar initiatives of comparable complexity. Has clinical domain knowledge and expert technical knowledge of functional areas and programmatic knowledge across the broad range of information and security systems and informatics. Provides industry-leading insight into complex, cutting-edge endeavors. Participates on cross-cutting panels and committees to provide transfer of knowledge and expertise to project stakeholders. Serves as principal/senior source of information for all relevant domain activities as required. Possesses certification as BICSI Registered Communications Distributore Designer (RCDD).   Also includes CAPM (Certified Associate in Project Management).   Additional certifications may include: Secondary BICSI certification,  Avigilon/Access Control,  Avigilon/CCTV,  Axis, Belden, Digital Watchdog, Cambridge, Panduit, Leviton, Open Path, Atlona, RS2, STI and 3M Firestopping and lift certification.
